main event: On November 10, 1962, a moving target was detected inbound by ground radar in North Star Bay, Greenland, with military searches conducted without results.
interesting points: The sighting was reported as an inbound moving target at a specific time,The observation lasted for 106 minutes,Military aircraft conducted extensive searches over a large area (approximately 1000 square miles),The report concluded that the target might have been a balloon or aircraft but was classified as insufficient data for evaluation,No photographs were included in the report.
